Impedance spectroscopy measurement is a powerful technique to probe the physical processes, such as carrier transfer and recombination at internal interfaces, using a proper RC element [34, 35]. Mott-Schottky (MS) curves were also measured for methanol-treated and untreated hybrid solar cells. According to Anderson’s model, the capacitance is described by the following equation [36].1C−2=Vbi−VappA2qε0εrNA,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
